I dont think its so much about ethnicity as much a its enmeshment... that Barb seems entitled to fight for. I am a narcissist abuse survivor, and had my MIL, and SIL break me down to the core during tragic experiences of my life. They required my husband and I adhere to their wishes, without any empathy or understanding of the relationship we want to be with eachother. I'd never been in such a terrifying situation, and being ignored by their entire family was heartbreaking. All I wanted was them to love me and be accepted.

Thank God, my husband saw through their mask and manipulative behavior and chose to protect me from them. Till this day, they they continue to intrude and title me a villain for taking their 38 year old son that I have been married to for over 11 years

snippet.textDisplay: Maybe Barb shouldn't have been as blunt as she was, although I think she felt like she had to defend herself as a result of backlash and ridicule she was getting on social media. I do agree with Chris that criticizing her son(no matter how much of it was warranted) on television was uncalled for. I do have to say though, that I thought Madison was very  disrespectful to Barb. As a mother of a male, courteousy and respect toward your elders go a looong way. Drawing a line  in the sand between a mother and a son, especially a son that obviously close (although, perhaps a little too close--not my business though), is not the most intelligent move.

snippet.textDisplay: My Mom and I usually watch the bachelor together and love the time we spend talking etc. I know how Men tend to want the girl that presents the most resistance. Peter doesn't seem like he's got a lot of experience in relationships so it's completely normal he would choose Madison. As for Barb, She's his Mom. She's angry because she's been there to pick up the pieces each time her son is destroyed by a love that he wanted but didn't work and she's mad he's done exactly what I said above. Listen parents out there: As the Mother of a 23 yr old Man I can say with a lot of experience DON'T let your heart, anger or pride take over when you show your opinion towards a particular relationship or against one. Our children are naturally wanting to do things their own way, on their own so just like Chris said if you tell them to or not to do something thats their decision they will most certainly go with the opposite of what you want them to do.

snippet.textDisplay: I have so many questions. Why did Chris interfere, and personally go speak to Madison after Hannah and Peter broke up? I don't ever recall this happening before. Why did Peter need closure with Hannah B, after he had proposed to Hannah Ann? I thought he said during his season, that he already had closure. Why would Madison ever consider giving him a chance? He is so immature, a mama's boy. Why do they need to have the parents there? I am so over people saying that family is important, and his Mom has unconditional love. Barb is a controlling, obsessive person, she needs to let her son live his own life; make his own mistakes. Doesn't want him to be hurt, shocker, but everyone gets hurts in life, he will survive. Barb, cut the chord, and get some therapy. Peter, ask your Mom, if she can give you your bills bag, and for f*** sake, move out. Word of advice to the producers of The Bachelor/Bachelorette, never have the parents in the audience again. Complete train wreck.
